<div id="pf19" class="pf w0 hb" data-page-no="19"><div class="pc pc19 w0 hb"><div class="t m371 x1 h16 y3ce ff3 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">LESSON 3 July 13-19 </div><div class="t m297 x51 h24 yd3 ff1 fs15 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">3 Thc2 Fin</div><div class="t m372 xae h25 yd3 ff5 fs15 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">-</div><div class="t m373 x6e h26 y3cf ff5 fs16 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Et </div><div class="t m374 x91 h24 y3cf ff1 fs15 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">IDIFIE5cog </div><div class="t m375 x77 h16 y3d0 ff3 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">&quot;How should man be just with </div><div class="t m376 x52 h16 y3d1 ff3 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">sod?&quot; (Job 9:2). </div><div class="t m377 x77 h14 y3d2 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">This is probably the most </div><div class="t m378 x52 h14 y3d3 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">penetrating question raised in the </div><div class="t m379 x52 h14 y3d4 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">section under study in this </div><div class="t m37a x52 h14 y3d5 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">lessonâ€”Job 3 through 11. These </div><div class="t m27f x52 h14 y2e ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">chapters include six speeches: Job </div><div class="t m37b x52 h14 y3d6 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">(3:1-26), Eliphaz (4:1 through 5:27), </div><div class="t m37c x52 h14 y3d7 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Job 6:1 through 7:21), Bildad (8:1-22), </div><div class="t m37d x52 h14 y3d8 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Job (9:1 through 10:22), Zophar </div><div class="t m37e x52 h14 y3d9 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">(11:1-20). These speeches represent </div><div class="t m37f x52 h14 y3da ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">the first of three dialogues or cycles </div><div class="t m380 x52 h14 y3db ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">that continue through the thirty-first </div><div class="t m381 x52 h14 y3dc ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">chapter. </div><div class="t m382 x77 h14 y31 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">It should be pointed out that many </div><div class="t m383 x52 h14 y3dd ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">expositors begin the first dialogue </div><div class="t m384 x52 h14 y3de ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">with chapter four and continue it </div><div class="t m385 x52 h14 y3df ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">through chapter fourteen. The writer </div><div class="t m386 x52 h14 y3e0 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">of these lessons feels that each </div><div class="t m387 x52 h14 y3e1 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">dialogue or cycle begins with a speech </div><div class="t m388 x52 h14 y3e2 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">by Job rather than with a speech by </div><div class="t m389 x52 h14 y3e3 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Efiphaz. This is the structure followed </div><div class="t m38a x0 h14 y3e4 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">in the </div><div class="t m38b x47 h14 y3e4 ff6 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">S.D.A. Bible Commentary. </div><div class="t m38c x52 h14 y3e5 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">However, this is a matter of opinion </div><div class="t m38d x0 h14 y3e6 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">and does not affect the message of the </div><div class="t m38e x0 h14 y3e7 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">book. </div><div class="t m38f x77 h14 y3e8 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Job 3, as pointed out in part 6 of </div><div class="t m390 x0 h14 y3e9 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">lesson 2, begins with a passage </div><div class="t m391 x0 h14 y3ea ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">reflecting gloom and darkness. Job  </div><div class="t m392 x93 h14 y3eb ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">curses the day he was born. He longs </div><div class="t m393 x93 h14 y3ec ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">for the grave: &quot;There the wicked cease </div><div class="t m394 x93 h14 y3ed ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">from troubling; and there the weary </div><div class="t m395 x93 h14 y3d2 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">be at rest. There the prisoners rest </div><div class="t m396 x93 h14 y3d3 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">together; they hear not the voice of </div><div class="t m1e7 x93 h14 y3d4 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">the oppressor. The small and great are </div><div class="t m397 x93 h14 y3ee ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">there; and the servant is free from his </div><div class="t m398 x93 h14 y2e ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">master. Wherefore is light given to </div><div class="t m399 x93 h14 y3ef ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">him that is in misery, and life unto the </div><div class="t m39a x93 h14 y3f0 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">bitter in soul; which long for death, </div><div class="t m39b x93 h14 y3d8 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">but it cometh not; and dig for it more </div><div class="t m39c x93 h14 y3d9 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">than for hid treasures; which rejoice </div><div class="t m39d x93 h14 y3da ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">exceedingly, and are glad, when they </div><div class="t m39e x93 h14 y3db ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">can find the grave&quot; (verses 17-22). </div><div class="t m389 x58 h14 y3f1 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">The final verses of this sad chapter </div><div class="t m395 x93 h14 y31 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">are well rendered in the TEV: </div><div class="t m39f x27 h14 y3f2 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">&quot;Instead of eating, I mourn, </div><div class="t m3a0 x3c h14 y3f3 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">and I can never stop groaning. </div><div class="t m3a1 x27 h14 y3df ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Everything I fear and dread comes </div><div class="t m3a2 xc h14 y3e0 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">true. </div><div class="t m3a3 x27 h14 y3e1 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">I have no peace, no rest, </div><div class="t m3a4 x3c h14 y3f4 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">and my troubles never end&quot; </div><div class="t m4f xaf h14 y3f5 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">(verses 24-26). </div><div class="t m3a5 x27 h14 y3f6 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">The dialogue begins with this </div><div class="t m3a6 x2f h14 y3f7 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">expression of discouragement </div><div class="t m3a7 x2f h14 y3f8 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">including the entire third chapter. It is </div><div class="t m266 x2f h14 y3e7 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">to this melancholy complaint that </div><div class="t m3a8 x2f h14 y3f9 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Eliphaz responds in chapters four and </div><div class="t m3a9 x2f h14 y3fa ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">five. </div><div class="t m3aa x27 h14 y3ea ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">The limits of our Sabbath School </div><div class="t m3ab x2f h14 y3fb ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">lesson make it impossible to cover </div><div class="t mc6 x2f h14 y3fc ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">every verse. Selections are made in an </div><div class="t m3ac x2f h14 y3fd ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">endeavor to recapture the basic </div><div class="t m63 x2f h14 y3fe ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">message of Job. It is urged that each </div><div class="t m13e x2f h14 y3ff ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">student of these lessons read the </div><div class="t m3ad x2f h14 y400 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">entire passage, including the verses </div><div class="t m3ae x2f h14 y401 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">that are not specifically dealt with in </div><div class="t m3af x2f h14 y402 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">the lessons. </div><div class="t m2af x2f h16 y86 ff3 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">DAILY HIGHLIGHTS </div><div class="t m63 x2f h16 y403 ff3 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">1. </div><div class="t m3b0 x59 h16 y404 ff3 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">A Wrong Answer </div><div class="t m213 xb0 h16 y405 ff3 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">(Job 4:7-9) </div><div class="t m65 x2f h16 y406 ff3 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">2. </div><div class="t m343 xb0 h16 y406 ff3 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">False Friends </div><div class="t m47 xb0 h16 y407 ff3 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">(Job 6:15-21) </div><div class="t m67 x2f h16 y408 ff3 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">3. </div><div class="t m3b1 xb0 h16 y408 ff3 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Job Challenges God </div><div class="t m98 xb0 h16 y409 ff3 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">(Job 7:19-21)</div><div class="t m3b2 x89 h16 y40a ff3 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">- </div><div class="t m3b3 x89 h16 y40a ff3 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"> </div><div class="t m69 x2f h16 y40b ff3 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">4. </div><div class="t m3b4 xb0 h16 y40b ff3 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Ancient Tradition Defended </div><div class="t m98 xb0 h16 y40c ff3 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">(Job 8:11-13) </div><div class="t m6b x2f h16 y40d ff3 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">5. </div><div class="t m296 xb0 h16 y40d ff3 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">God&apos;s Power and Job&apos;s Weakness </div><div class="t m3b5 xb0 h16 y40e ff3 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">(Job 9:19, 20) </div><div class="t m6d x2f h16 y40f ff3 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">6. </div><div class="t m297 xb0 h16 y40f ff3 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Repentance Urged </div><div class="t m3b6 xb0 h16 y410 ff3 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">(Job 11:13, 14) </div></div><div class="pi" data-data='{"ctm":[1.000000,0.000000,0.000000,1.000000,0.000000,0.000000]}'></div></div>
